name: real_world_invalid_email_local_part_over_64_octets
description: |
  The local-part is 65 ASCII octets, one beyond the SMTP maximum. Character-
  based limits and off-by-one comparisons frequently accept this boundary.

  RFC 5321 section 4.5.3.1.1 limits local-parts to 64 octets:
  https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc5321.html#section-4.5.3.1.1
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
tags:
  - "real-world"
  - "email"
  - "email-address"
  - "smtp"
  - "invalid-email"
  - "invalid"
  - "local-part"
  - "length-limit"
  - "65-octets"
  - "boundary"
---
abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789abc@example.com
